# Database — Supabase (recommended) or local PostgreSQL.
#
# --- Supabase ---
# Your project: https://fzvoarlgtdpajrbhemft.supabase.co
# 1. Project Settings → Database → Connection string → URI → "Transaction" (pooler, port 6543).
# 2. Copy the URI, add ?pgbouncer=true at the end, then set DATABASE_URL below.
#    Format: postgresql://postgres.fzvoarlgtdpajrbhemft:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true
#    (Get the exact host and password from the dashboard; URL-encode the password if it has special chars.)
# For local dev use the same pooler URL. For Prisma Studio you can use "Session" (direct, port 5432) if needed.
#
# --- Local PostgreSQL ---
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/pcc?schema=public"
#
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/pcc?schema=public"

# NextAuth. Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32. REQUIRED in production.
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-secret-here"
# Local: http://localhost:3000. Production (e.g. Vercel): MUST be https://your-domain.com
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# Vercel/production: STRONGLY RECOMMENDED. Without Redis, rate limits are per serverless instance (easier to bypass).
# REDIS_URL="redis://..." or Upstash/Redis Cloud URL

# Optional: AI weekly insights (get key from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)
# OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
